  "manufacturing": {
    "method": "azo coupling synthesis",
    "description": "Synthesized through chemical azo coupling reactions. As a bis-azo dye, it contains two azo bonds (N=N functional groups) created through diazotization and coupling processes. The resulting disodium salt provides a brown color and occurs as a brown powder or granules, used primarily to mimic chocolate or cocoa coloring without using actual cocoa."
  },
